# Project Rules

> ⚠️ **IMPORTANT**: Before completing ANY task, always update @docs/architecture.md!

## 1. Architectural Rules

- **ALWAYS** follow architectural rules from @docs/arch-rules.md
- **ALWAYS** apply business requirements from @requirements.md

## 2. Architecture Documentation Updates

**MANDATORY** update @docs/architecture.md for any changes:

### When to update:

- Adding new components or files
- Changing API endpoints or their behavior
- Modifying caching system
- Security changes (cookies, authentication)
- Configuration updates (TypeScript, Docker, etc.)
- Adding new dependencies or tools
- Changes in logging or monitoring

### How to update:

1. **Add to "Recent Changes" section** brief description of changes
2. **Update relevant sections** (API, components, caching, etc.)
3. **Add code examples** if implementation changed
4. **Update tables** (endpoints, roles, components)

**Detailed templates:** See @.cursor/rules/architecture-updates.md

## 3. Pre-completion Checklist

Before completing any task:

- [ ] Verified changes comply with @docs/arch-rules.md
- [ ] Ensured requirements from @requirements.md are met
- [ ] Updated @docs/architecture.md with change descriptions
- [ ] Added code examples if needed